1
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Totò, Peppino and the Evilwoman

2
00:00:34,050 --> 00:00:39,900
(subtitles by Simone)

3
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:46,160
(revision by Claudio)

4
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:59,000
A liar woman has left me...

5
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:03,000
- You're always in between!
- Damn!

6
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:04,960
Did I hurt you?

7
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,500
Think about your health!

8
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:08,000
Health, what health?

9
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,960
Here it is: Mezzacapa ("Halfhead") Farm.
Even the name is unpleasant.

10
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:19,000
I don't like it too, but I don't know
why we have to hate him.

11
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:21,000
Because you never understand anything.

12
00:02:21,030 --> 00:02:23,010
Mezzacapa is our neighbour, right?

13
00:02:23,050 --> 00:02:25,000
His field borders on ours, right?

14
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:25,960
I don't like him.

15
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,000
All neighbours are unpleasant and hideous.

16
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Check if he's at the window.

17
00:02:32,030 --> 00:02:33,000
No.

18
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Be quick.

19
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,000
- Who was that?
- Don't ask.

20
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Same story. Those two are the Caponi ("Bigheads")
brothers. If I catch them...

21
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
He heard you.
He heard you.

22
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
Good morning, Peppino.
Good morning, Totò.

23
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,000
You put your feet
under the wheel.

24
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:23,000
Damn it!

25
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
I was waiting for you yesterday.

26
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:25,960
I couldn't come. My wife was sick.

27
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:30,000
No, you mustn't be late,
otherwise i'll change metayer.

28
00:03:30,030 --> 00:03:30,960
No, why?

29
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Then, you owe 60.
And 40 of the old bill.

30
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:36,960
That makes 100.

31
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,000
That makes 100.
Neat, neat: net weight.

32
00:03:39,030 --> 00:03:41,010
Net weight: here 10,000 lire are missing.

33
00:03:41,050 --> 00:03:43,000
Sorry, they were in this other department.

34
00:03:43,820 --> 00:03:47,180
- Ok, ok. - And now, you owe me
12,000 lire.

35
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:51,800
- 12,000 I used to pay the vet for the cow.
- Yes, yes, I remember.

36
00:03:51,830 --> 00:03:56,370
The cow died and so the two veals.
I've... I've said enough, I've said.

37
00:03:56,410 --> 00:03:59,680
- One moment, I paid 12,000 lire, Peppino.
- He's said enough, you'll never see them.

38
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:02,600
- How I'll never see them?
- Tell me Nicola, what do you owe me?

39
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:04,720
Nothing, I already paid you in advance.

40
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:07,870
Ok, but now it's summer,
pay me this in advance.

41
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:11,410
Don Antonio, I already paid you '56, '57 and '58.

42
00:04:11,450 --> 00:04:14,500
- But '59 is uncovered.
- You like jokes, but I get angry.

43
00:04:14,540 --> 00:04:17,560
Good morning, Don Antonio,
did you bring me a present?

44
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,130
Of course, turn around.

45
00:04:20,020 --> 00:04:20,850
Close your eyes.

46
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:26,450
Open your eyes.

47
00:04:26,490 --> 00:04:29,840
- Oh, it's beautiful! -You like it?
- Thanks, Don Antonio -You're welcome.

48
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:32,690
See you later, eh? Bye!

49
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:38,010
- It's 27,000 lire.
- 27,000 lire.

50
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:40,000
Plus... plus... plus...

51
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:42,620
- Give here.
- I was counting them for you.

52
00:04:42,650 --> 00:04:43,620
I count them myself.

53
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:49,230
So we're even...
and with you, as well.

54
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:53,690
Madam?

55
00:04:56,340 --> 00:05:01,180
Oh, you're here at last!
I've been waiting for you for two hours!

56
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:03,710
And I can't close the luggage
without underwear.

57
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:07,320
- What you're looking at?
- Nothing... I was looking for you.

58
00:05:07,350 --> 00:05:10,020
Ah... I know who you're looking for.

59
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:15,130
But you, my son, Mr. Gianni,
you must forget him.

60
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,830
You and all the girls around, right?

61
00:05:16,860 --> 00:05:17,790
Let's go!

62
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:19,840
Madam, I'm a serious girl!

63
00:05:19,870 --> 00:05:21,490
Maybe you are...

64
00:05:23,050 --> 00:05:24,860
but you iron very badly!

65
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,910
Look at this... Is this ironed?

66
00:05:26,940 --> 00:05:28,440
Well ironed?

67
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,910
My girl...

68
00:05:29,950 --> 00:05:36,190
With this my son has to take his degree
in front of the biggest scientists of the world!

69
00:05:36,230 --> 00:05:37,650
Alright...

70
00:05:37,690 --> 00:05:38,930
I'll take care of that.

71
00:05:38,970 --> 00:05:41,480
Let's go upstairs, hurry up,
it's late.

72
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:44,510
And Gianni has to leave for Milano.
Come on! Come on!

73
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:45,910
Where are my brothers?

74
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,600
They'll make him lose his train.

75
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:52,020
- They're outside.
- Doing what?

76
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:59,420
You look like the National Bank cashier.
Counting, counting, but what d'ya count?

77
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:02,580
Beast! Spend your money! Have fun!

78
00:06:02,710 --> 00:06:06,030
Life is short! Death can comes
any time! Look at me!

79
00:06:06,060 --> 00:06:08,230
One can also live 100 years.

80
00:06:08,260 --> 00:06:09,290
And then?

81
00:06:09,330 --> 00:06:10,330
I've said enough, I've said.

82
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,050
By the way...

83
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:14,340
- Oh, sorry.
- By the way...

84
00:06:14,370 --> 00:06:15,770
You owe 40,000 lire.

85
00:06:15,810 --> 00:06:18,140
About that consignment of oil of the last month.

86
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:21,470
-Consignment? Consignment is consigned!
-No, no, not for me.

87
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:24,970
Ok, ok. What's that?
You're in hurry?

88
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:27,400
You just said one can live 100 years.

89
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:28,880
But death can comes any time.

90
00:06:28,910 --> 00:06:30,510
C'mon, c'mon, hurry up.

91
00:06:30,550 --> 00:06:31,760
Hurry up, hurry up...

92
00:06:31,790 --> 00:06:32,970
It depends on you.

93
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:33,930
How?

94
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:37,220
Well, these ones, you take them with you?

95
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:39,110
Yes, I put them aside.

96
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,380
In the same place.

97
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:41,590
I put them aside.

98
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:44,670
Right, if somebody has found a safe place,
it's no use to change it.

99
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:45,630
Then, go!

100
00:06:45,670 --> 00:06:46,880
You put them in the same place.

101
00:06:46,890 --> 00:06:47,850
I put them aside.

102
00:06:47,890 --> 00:06:49,630
Mine is a friend's advice.

103
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:50,600
And brother's.

104
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,500
And my advice is to go, now!

105
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:54,580
You put them there, do you?

106
00:06:55,070 --> 00:06:56,330
I put them aside.
Ouch!

107
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,060
- Just go!
- I'm going.

108
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:02,420
Don't change the place!
Don't change the place!

109
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:09,050
- Go!
- You stingy peasant!

110
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,940
Dear brother,

111
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:01,260
here are your 40,000 lire.

112
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:02,970
Ah, very well.

113
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,650
One is missing.

114
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,840
- How's that?
- One is missing.

115
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,850
Here it is. A bit of distraction.

116
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:10,810
It happens.

117
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:14,480
- So, there's nothing left?
- We're even. - We're even.

118
00:09:14,510 --> 00:09:16,900
- The game is over.

119
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,760
Now, I'd need a little favour.

120
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,940
- What? - We have
to start a new one.

121
00:09:21,190 --> 00:09:23,090
You have to lend me 80,000 lire.

122
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,420
Hmm, not 80,000.

123
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:28,990
I can lend you these 40,000 lire.

124
00:09:29,020 --> 00:09:29,590
Here they are.

125
00:09:33,530 --> 00:09:35,790
- Distraction.
- It happens.

126
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:38,630
- Listen...
- You already owe me 40,000 lire.

127
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:39,390
Why?

128
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:41,900
Didn't I give them to you before?

129
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,500
I gave you 40,000 lire.

130
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:44,540
And game is over.

131
00:09:44,580 --> 00:09:48,050
Then I asked you 80,000 lire,
but you could only lend me 40,000.

132
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:51,420
- How many lire are missing
to get to 80? - 40.

133
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:53,330
Then you owe me 40,000 lire,
right?

134
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,170
It's simple. Maths is not an opinion.

135
00:09:55,210 --> 00:09:59,020
My dear brother, you need
an accountant.

136
00:09:59,050 --> 00:09:59,710
You're ignorant.

137
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:03,490
I'd like to know what you do
with all this money.

138
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,010
You need lots of money.

139
00:10:05,050 --> 00:10:07,430
I'm not like you.
I'm a man who lives...

140
00:10:07,460 --> 00:10:08,360
lives and knows how to live.

141
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,790
Modestly speaking I know
how to dress myself.

142
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:11,780
Some girls...
I enjoy myself...

143
00:10:11,810 --> 00:10:13,700
Presents...
The necklace...

144
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:15,970
Those dogs, he calls them girls...

145
00:10:16,010 --> 00:10:19,270
One day you'll end up there,
I'm telling you.

146
00:10:19,310 --> 00:10:21,290
- What does it mean there?
- I've said enough, I have.

147
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:23,140
You said nothing!

148
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:26,060
You see, for example,
you stingy man,

149
00:10:26,070 --> 00:10:28,170
Of these 40,000 you just lend me,

150
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:30,280
20,000 are a present to our nephew.

151
00:10:30,310 --> 00:10:31,860
- Understand?
- Bad idea.

152
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:32,830
Why?

153
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:34,240
Very bad. That's a young guy,
you're spoiling him.

154
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:34,680
Spoling him?

155
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:37,750
Look at me. I give him healthy things.

156
00:10:37,780 --> 00:10:39,950
A nice caciotta cheese, and he's okay.

157
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,650
So he's in Napoli, downtown,

158
00:10:41,690 --> 00:10:43,460
he wants to go to the theatre with a girl,

159
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:46,730
and he goes to the counter
with a slice of caciotta! Peppino!

160
00:10:49,910 --> 00:10:52,270
So there they are!

161
00:10:52,310 --> 00:10:54,600
Antonio! Peppino!

162
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:56,020
Gianni is ready, c'mon!

163
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:58,090
Hurry up! The train won't stay there waiting!

164
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:59,780
Mom, relax, there's still time.

165
00:10:59,820 --> 00:11:01,490
- Still time, What time is it?
- What time is it?

166
00:11:02,940 --> 00:11:05,920
- Mine is slow.
- And mine is fast.

167
00:11:05,950 --> 00:11:06,870
What time is it?

168
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:07,750
A quarter past five.

169
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:09,150
Here's a quarter to five.

170
00:11:09,190 --> 00:11:11,440
- Let's meet us.
- Then it's five.

171
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:12,990
There's still an hour.

172
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,310
Beautiful son of mine, please, study!

173
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:17,230
Honour your father's memory!

174
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:20,540
He wanted you to become a
great doctor so much.

175
00:11:21,850 --> 00:11:23,980
Don't worry, mom,
everything's gonna be alright.

176
00:11:24,010 --> 00:11:25,280
Have a nice trip, doctor.

177
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:26,410
I'm no doctor, yet.

178
00:11:26,450 --> 00:11:29,100
You will, you will.

179
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:31,720
With your...
I've said enough.

180
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:33,530
- What did you say?
- I've said enough.

181
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:34,460
- Bye Mariangela.

182
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:37,540
Because of hurrying I was forgetting
the passito wine.

183
00:11:37,570 --> 00:11:38,540
Antonio, Gianni's bag!

184
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:43,590
-I can take it myself. -No, you must study.
Uncle Antonio e uncle Peppino will take care.

185
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:46,060
- Uncle Antonio e uncle Peppino.
- It's us.

186
00:11:46,310 --> 00:11:47,480
The bottle.

187
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:50,530
-Did you hear? Uncle Antonio e uncle Peppino.
-We'll take care.

188
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:53,500
The boy must study.

189
00:11:58,470 --> 00:11:59,750
Slow down!

190
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:13,320
A liar woman left me...

191
00:12:14,930 --> 00:12:15,650
Did I hurt you?

192
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:19,650
But your head is always in the middle.
Think about health.

193
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:26,060
Check out, is he at the window?

194
00:12:27,690 --> 00:12:29,200
- No. - Take.

195
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,540
- Keep it a while.
- What is it?

196
00:12:39,010 --> 00:12:40,980
- What has he done?
- Nothing. He threw a stone.

197
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,400
Mezzacapa, we don't like him.

198
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:46,150
So, everytime we buzz around,
we throw him stones.

199
00:12:46,180 --> 00:12:47,150
Haven't you become children, do you?

200
00:12:47,180 --> 00:12:48,930
What children.

201
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:51,200
Anyway, it's him who throws, not me.

202
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:01,950
- Write! - Write!

203
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:39,370
- Don't shoot.
- Let me do it, let me do it.

204
00:13:43,830 --> 00:13:46,170
How can you smile?
He could hit us!

205
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:48,080
He could hit you, not me!

206
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,990
Why me? You threw the stone!

207
00:14:21,870 --> 00:14:23,590
- Are you bored?
- It's not bad, thanks.

208
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:25,600
I see, and you know why?

209
00:14:26,050 --> 00:14:27,740
Because here there's too much crowd,
too much light,

210
00:14:28,210 --> 00:14:30,720
and because we're not alone,
you and me.

211
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,820
I have been waiting for 30 centuries.

212
00:14:33,850 --> 00:14:35,200
But I've been in Napoli since a month.

213
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:36,540
Exactly. Each day a century.

214
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:40,410
Listen, let's make it,
an English-style escape.

215
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:41,710
Come to my place.

216
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,590
Are you sure I'd enjoy myself
more than here?

217
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:45,200
I'm the best partner.

218
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,900
Sure, you're a nobleman,
you're rich

219
00:14:46,930 --> 00:14:48,030
haughty...

220
00:14:48,070 --> 00:14:49,210
Yes, indeed!

221
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,360
very haughty.

222
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,960
Hey, you two, did you really decide
to stay together all the time?

223
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:57,400
I'll wait you on the stairs in 5 minutes.

224
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:59,420
- It's my turn, now.
- As you prefer.

225
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:06,620
It's so crowded on this terrace.

226
00:15:06,620 --> 00:15:08,710
- But you invited them.
- Yes, that's true.

227
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:10,210
And now I can't throw them away.

228
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:14,640
But I have a bottle of champagne for the two
of us, there, on the other balcony.

229
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:16,840
Can we drink it you and me,
totally alone,

230
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,680
under the moonlight?

231
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,170
And...?

232
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:21,400
Then?

233
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,890
Well... let's not be in advance
of our time!

234
00:15:23,930 --> 00:15:26,450
Yes, good, let's not be it.

235
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:33,490
Remo, you're a very bad
amphitryon.

236
00:15:33,490 --> 00:15:35,820
You let anyone thirsty
and you don't care.

237
00:15:35,860 --> 00:15:38,680
- Go and care of your guests.
- Gabriella, you're so boring.

238
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:46,210
- Well, what's up?
- I got bored.

239
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:48,180
- I wanna go away.
- What's wrong with you?

240
00:15:48,740 --> 00:15:51,260
Ah... All these hands upon me...

241
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,620
Dear, try to be rational.

242
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:55,690
Gabriella... I dance samba only with you.

243
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:11,270
Stay near to me,

244
00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:14,610
one more night,

245
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:20,050
you can never know,

246
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:23,600
how dear you are,

247
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:30,210
a caress is like the sky,
a caress from the moon,

248
00:17:31,030 --> 00:17:36,890
a caress is like the sea,
a caress of the sand,

249
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:39,880
let me sleep.

250
00:17:47,370 --> 00:17:48,670
-Good evening.
-Good evening,

251
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:51,120
I'm sorry, I didn't know that...

252
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:52,830
Where are you from?

253
