00:45:05,330 --> 00:45:06,050
Hey,

776
00:45:25,100 --> 00:45:26,310
Hallo?

777
00:45:26,770 --> 00:45:27,800
Yes, Gabriella, it's me.

778
00:45:28,690 --> 00:45:30,230
I'm fine, very fine.

779
00:45:31,290 --> 00:45:32,600
Of course it is still on.

780
00:45:33,790 --> 00:45:36,380
Listen, would you mind your own business?

781
00:45:37,320 --> 00:45:39,160
Do I come to theatre?
Do I make my duty? Yes.

782
00:45:39,160 --> 00:45:40,600
So don't bother me.

783
00:45:41,390 --> 00:45:43,750
Yes, yes, you can tell the manager, too.

784
00:45:48,420 --> 00:45:50,210
Be damned the day I gave you that key!

785
00:45:50,610 --> 00:45:52,940
Is it possible that I have to come
to my house through the sea?

786
00:45:52,940 --> 00:45:54,310
How boring you are!

787
00:45:54,310 --> 00:45:55,910
Next Monday I'm off.

788
00:45:55,910 --> 00:45:57,410
Great. Where do you go?

789
00:45:57,410 --> 00:45:58,610
To Milano with her.

790
00:45:58,610 --> 00:46:00,530
To Milano? And who gives you the money?

791
00:46:00,980 --> 00:46:04,810
Yesterday I met a family friend. No, a family enemy.
He lent me 300,000 lire.

792
00:46:04,810 --> 00:46:05,670
Lucky you!

793
00:46:05,670 --> 00:46:07,130
Did you bring me my clothes?

794
00:46:07,770 --> 00:46:08,690
Yes, here it is.

795
00:46:09,180 --> 00:46:09,750
Catch it!

796
00:46:19,220 --> 00:46:22,060
130, 140, 150.

797
00:46:22,060 --> 00:46:25,320
Here you are. This is my part,
the rest is my brother's.

798
00:46:26,670 --> 00:46:29,590
Here it is. These are my 150,000 lire.

799
00:46:29,720 --> 00:46:32,640
Very well. Plus 150 it's 300.
Here the bill.

800
00:46:32,810 --> 00:46:34,550
What a shame, what a shame!

801
00:46:34,560 --> 00:46:38,700
Shame... why do you complain?
I've always told you that he's a... a...

802
00:46:38,940 --> 00:46:40,950
-What?
-I've said enough.

803
00:46:41,880 --> 00:46:43,570
When you say ' I've said enough',
you make get angry.

804
00:46:43,980 --> 00:46:44,570
This ' I've said enough'
makes me get angry.

805
00:46:45,420 --> 00:46:46,800
Because you say, you say
and you never say anything.

806
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:49,170
Do I never say anything?
You call this anything?

807
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:50,670
You call this anything?!

808
00:46:50,670 --> 00:46:53,890
Stop that. Let me sit.

809
00:46:54,250 --> 00:46:56,060
Listen, Mr. Halfhead,
where did you see my son?

810
00:46:56,590 --> 00:46:58,500
Madam, I've already told you,
I've seen in Napoli.

811
00:46:59,420 --> 00:47:00,490
It happened by chance.

812
00:47:00,570 --> 00:47:04,560
One night I was walking along via Caracciolo,
when I heard someone calling me.

813
00:47:05,130 --> 00:47:06,870
I turned around and there was your son.

814
00:47:07,460 --> 00:47:09,920
He came out from an expensive restaurant
together with a beautiful girl.

815
00:47:10,500 --> 00:47:12,780
I got closer and he introduced me to the girl.

816
00:47:12,780 --> 00:47:16,480
-Mezzacapa -he said- this is
my girlfriend.   -Girlfriend?

817
00:47:16,480 --> 00:47:17,750
Yes, girlfriend.

818
00:47:17,750 --> 00:47:19,190
We took a coffee together,

819
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:22,200
and at one point he called me
in a corner,

820
00:47:23,060 --> 00:47:24,920
and he asked me 300,000 lire.

821
00:47:25,310 --> 00:47:28,100
What could I do?
Not giving them to him?

822
00:47:28,100 --> 00:47:28,760
No.

823
00:47:29,470 --> 00:47:31,210
I know you since a long time.

824
00:47:31,870 --> 00:47:34,460
I know you as honest people.

825
00:47:34,950 --> 00:47:36,480
-Sorry.
-No problem.

826
00:47:38,450 --> 00:47:39,540
I had to lend him those money.

827
00:47:39,550 --> 00:47:43,240
Of course, I made him signing a bill.

828
00:47:44,060 --> 00:47:45,170
Listen, I go to Napoli.

829
00:47:45,450 --> 00:47:47,540
-But where...   -I go.
-Where do you wanna go?!

830
00:47:48,410 --> 00:47:50,120
What do you think, that Napoli
is just down the corner?

831
00:47:50,130 --> 00:47:53,200
Why do you go to Napoli?
Do you think it's like...

832
00:47:53,940 --> 00:47:54,710
I've said enough.

833
00:47:55,370 --> 00:47:57,780
-It's useless you go to Napoli.
-Why is it useless?

834
00:47:58,160 --> 00:48:00,610
Because... there's no one left in Napoli.

835
00:48:00,610 --> 00:48:01,720
Has it been evacuated?

836
00:48:01,720 --> 00:48:02,660
Has it been emptied?

837
00:48:03,280 --> 00:48:05,070
I didn't mean that.

838
00:48:05,570 --> 00:48:07,820
I meant that your nephew isn't in Napoli anymore.

839
00:48:08,180 --> 00:48:10,960
-Because he followed the lost
women's caravel.   -What?

840
00:48:11,180 --> 00:48:13,230
Women in Napoli lost their caravans.

841
00:48:13,620 --> 00:48:15,200
No, what have you understood?!

842
00:48:16,380 --> 00:48:19,120
The lost women's caravel is a vaudeville.

843
00:48:19,120 --> 00:48:22,360
Understand? The lost women,
in Napoli, looked for the villains.

844
00:48:22,770 --> 00:48:26,100
In Napoli, women lost their caravans
because of the villains.

845
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:27,600
What are you saying, for God's sake?

846
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:28,630
Haven't you understood?

847
00:48:28,630 --> 00:48:31,550
Mr. Halfhead, you must be objective with us.

848
00:48:31,550 --> 00:48:34,500
These subtle sentences don't convince us, ok?

849
00:48:34,500 --> 00:48:35,370
Let's speak clear.

850
00:48:35,370 --> 00:48:36,400
-Clearer than th...
-Clear!

851
00:48:38,170 --> 00:48:39,340
Who lost these caravans?

852
00:48:39,340 --> 00:48:41,010
Nobody lost them.

853
00:48:43,220 --> 00:48:45,270
The caravel is a show,

854
00:48:45,770 --> 00:48:48,430
and Gianni's girlfriend is a singer.

855
00:48:49,590 --> 00:48:50,600
And I mean seriously.

856
00:48:51,080 --> 00:48:52,130
If I can speak freely,

857
00:48:52,130 --> 00:48:53,500
this girlfriend

858
00:48:54,080 --> 00:48:55,230
is a beautiful girl.

859
00:48:55,690 --> 00:48:57,910
Tall, blonde, well-rounded.

860
00:48:58,790 --> 00:48:59,650
She has beautiful legs.

861
00:48:59,650 --> 00:49:01,390
How did you manage to see her legs?

862
00:49:02,020 --> 00:49:04,490
Me? Only me?
A half of Napoli saw them!

863
00:49:05,940 --> 00:49:08,160
At the theatre, it's normal,
you pay the ticket,

864
00:49:08,160 --> 00:49:09,840
you sit on your chair and you see the legs.

865
00:49:09,840 --> 00:49:10,770
Oh my God!

866
00:49:10,770 --> 00:49:12,440
What are these? Legs on payment?

867
00:49:12,440 --> 00:49:13,950
Calm down, calm down.

868
00:49:13,950 --> 00:49:15,860
No, no, now you have to be objective.

869
00:49:16,070 --> 00:49:18,220
-Poor son of mine.
-Calm down, Mrs. Lucia, calm down.

870
00:49:18,220 --> 00:49:19,320
Listen, Halfhead,

871
00:49:19,640 --> 00:49:20,630
you said they left.

872
00:49:20,630 --> 00:49:21,740
Where did they go?

873
00:49:22,440 --> 00:49:23,050
To Milano.

874
00:49:23,810 --> 00:49:25,610
Then, let's go to Milano now.

875
00:49:25,610 --> 00:49:27,510
-Are you crazy?
-Why?

876
00:49:27,510 --> 00:49:28,760
You can't go to Milano like this.

877
00:49:30,360 --> 00:49:31,410
To get to Milano you need,

878
00:49:31,960 --> 00:49:33,250
at least, four days on the sea.

879
00:49:33,250 --> 00:49:35,720
Maybe more, because then...

880
00:49:37,330 --> 00:49:38,410
He has said enough.

881
00:49:38,660 --> 00:49:40,940
What are you saying, please,

882
00:49:40,940 --> 00:49:42,050
sea? What sea?

883
00:49:42,450 --> 00:49:43,740
You go to Milano by land.

884
00:49:43,740 --> 00:49:44,470
On foot?

885
00:49:44,470 --> 00:49:45,420
On foot...

886
00:49:46,600 --> 00:49:48,120
Which country are you living in?

887
00:49:48,120 --> 00:49:49,370
On foot!

888
00:49:49,370 --> 00:49:50,140
Easy to say...

889
00:49:50,140 --> 00:49:51,740
You know where Milano is, don't you?

890
00:49:51,740 --> 00:49:52,800
In Calabria!

891
00:49:53,530 --> 00:49:54,440
In Sardinia, I made a mistake.

892
00:49:54,440 --> 00:49:55,910
Calabria, Sardinia...

893
00:49:55,910 --> 00:49:57,360
Milano is the capital of the North.

894
00:49:57,360 --> 00:49:58,190
We know that.

895
00:49:58,290 --> 00:49:59,410
Try to imagine, this is the "Boot".

896
00:49:59,410 --> 00:50:01,840
Up here there is the North,
down here the South.

897
00:50:01,840 --> 00:50:04,320
Ok, we are those who stay under the boot.

898
00:50:05,060 --> 00:50:05,760
The Southerners.

899
00:50:05,760 --> 00:50:07,130
North, South,

900
00:50:07,140 --> 00:50:10,130
I said I was going to Milano
and I will!

901
00:50:10,140 --> 00:50:12,410
If you want come with me,
otherwise I'll go alone.

902
00:50:12,550 --> 00:50:13,760
My son has got to study.

903
00:50:14,280 --> 00:50:16,580
My son has to leave that woman,
understand?

904
00:50:17,820 --> 00:50:20,020
Bless... bless... bless...

905
00:50:20,020 --> 00:50:22,630
Peppino, we have to go to Milano
with our sister.

906
00:50:22,630 --> 00:50:24,320
She can't go alone.

907
00:50:24,650 --> 00:50:26,010
Ok, let's go with her.

908
00:50:26,010 --> 00:50:29,280
Instead, we'd need someone
who gives us advice.

909
00:50:29,280 --> 00:50:30,950
Going to Milano is not easy.

910
00:50:30,950 --> 00:50:31,960
Someone?

911
00:50:33,030 --> 00:50:34,390
What am I doing here, then?

912
00:50:34,400 --> 00:50:35,880
Everybody calls me "the Milanese".

913
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:37,940
Halfhead, let's speak clearly.

914
00:50:37,940 --> 00:50:39,430
Have you ever really been to Milano?

915
00:50:39,640 --> 00:50:42,870
How haven't I? I made my military
service there.  In 1931.

916
00:50:42,870 --> 00:50:44,900
But what I mean, Halfhead,

917
00:50:45,550 --> 00:50:47,890
what the Milan people said
when they saw you?

918
00:50:48,600 --> 00:50:49,700
What should have they said?

919
00:50:49,700 --> 00:50:51,230
I mean, when you walked by the road...

920
00:50:52,070 --> 00:50:53,120
This stranger...

921
00:50:53,120 --> 00:50:54,280
Let's not be silly,

922
00:50:54,280 --> 00:50:57,080
they didn't notice me at all.
In Milano?

923
00:50:57,080 --> 00:50:59,750
You have no idea about what Milano is.

924
00:50:59,750 --> 00:51:00,790
They speak, they speak, don't they?

925
00:51:01,320 --> 00:51:01,930
Do they speak?

926
00:51:01,930 --> 00:51:03,740
Milano is a great city.

927
00:51:03,740 --> 00:51:05,250
They walk, they walk like us, don't they?

928
00:51:05,250 --> 00:51:07,240
Do they walk? There's a huge traffic.

929
00:51:07,750 --> 00:51:09,140
Indeed, you must be careful.

930
00:51:09,690 --> 00:51:11,700
Crossing the street is a dangerous thing, there.

931
00:51:11,700 --> 00:51:12,700
We'll never cross it!

932
00:51:12,710 --> 00:51:14,160
We won't even move!

933
00:51:14,160 --> 00:51:17,660
I must say that the weather isn't like here.

934
00:51:18,060 --> 00:51:19,330
There's a more rigid weather.

935
00:51:19,550 --> 00:51:21,550
-Wind, snow...
-Cold?

936
00:51:21,550 --> 00:51:23,560
Cold, the storms.

937
00:51:23,560 --> 00:51:24,220
The storks.

938
00:51:24,220 --> 00:51:26,130
There are storks?

939
00:51:27,740 --> 00:51:29,450
-On the road?
-On the road.

940
00:51:29,450 --> 00:51:31,010
On the road, everywhere.

941
00:51:31,010 --> 00:51:32,790
They go inside the buildings,
up the roofs...

942
00:51:33,090 --> 00:51:34,800
Water, wind and fog!

943
00:51:34,800 --> 00:51:36,220
Fog... fog...

944
00:51:36,220 --> 00:51:37,010
This frightens me.

945
00:51:37,010 --> 00:51:37,950
Anything else, but the fog...

946
00:51:37,950 --> 00:51:40,960
In Milano, when there's fog, you can't see.

947
00:51:40,960 --> 00:51:41,860
Good Lord!

948
00:51:42,930 --> 00:51:43,740
But who saw her?

949
00:51:43,740 --> 00:51:44,410
What?

950
00:51:45,300 --> 00:51:46,560
This Fog.

951
00:51:46,560 --> 00:51:47,270
Nobody.

952
00:51:47,270 --> 00:51:50,290
But, if people cannot see
when there's Fog in Milano...

953
00:51:50,520 --> 00:51:52,490
how can you see Fog is in Milano?

954
00:51:52,490 --> 00:51:55,470
No, it's something you don't touch, ok?

955
00:51:56,600 --> 00:51:57,310
Don't touch?

956
00:51:57,310 --> 00:51:58,660
-It's something that goes inside you.
-Don't touch her.

957
00:51:59,330 --> 00:52:03,060
But, apart this Fog,
I won't touch her for Christ's sake,

958
00:52:03,060 --> 00:52:06,990
if we have to meet with our nephew,

959
00:52:06,990 --> 00:52:08,370
and with this singer,

960
00:52:08,370 --> 00:52:09,640
how do we see them?
How do we find them?

961
00:52:09,640 --> 00:52:10,860
Right, I haven't thought about it.

962
00:52:11,250 --> 00:52:14,170
It's easy. The singer
has her name on the poster.

963
00:52:14,170 --> 00:52:16,620
Understand? In Milano,
when there is the fog,

964
00:52:16,620 --> 00:52:18,410
they put their names on the posters.

965
00:52:18,410 --> 00:52:20,230
"If you want to meet me, I'm here!"

966
00:52:21,460 --> 00:52:22,770
-A kind of signalling.
-Signalling.

967
00:52:22,780 --> 00:52:25,140
You see the name of the singer,
you go to the theatre.

968
00:52:26,060 --> 00:52:27,200
What is her name?

969
00:52:49,370 --> 00:52:52,470
Miss, this is from Grand Milan's direction,
with many congratulations.

970
00:53:03,960 --> 00:53:05,020
Are you happy, my dear?

971
00:53:05,110 --> 00:53:07,560
I'm so happy, my love,
but you shouldn't have done it.

972
00:53:07,570 --> 00:53:10,860
Should not? You make me study all day long,
tonight that is your birthday...

973
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:23,080
For you, miss.

974
00:53:24,070 --> 00:53:24,750
Thank you.

975
00:53:25,650 --> 00:53:26,280
Who's the sender?

976
00:53:26,820 --> 00:53:27,530
That gentleman over there.

977
00:53:34,500 --> 00:53:35,120
Who's he?

978
00:53:35,380 --> 00:53:37,120
I don't know.
It's the first time I see him.

979
00:53:37,120 --> 00:53:38,160
But he sends you flowers, doesn't he?

980
00:53:39,300 --> 00:53:41,960
Dear, you often forget I'm a showgirl.

981
00:53:42,520 --> 00:53:45,040
But you make me remember it.

982
00:53:45,040 --> 00:53:45,830
Gianni, please.

983
00:53:48,530 --> 00:53:50,650
Here they are, our doves!

984
00:53:51,970 --> 00:53:53,960
I didn't miss them.
Was it you who invited them?

985
00:53:54,560 --> 00:53:55,330
Me? Are you crazy?

986
00:53:56,140 --> 00:53:57,610
Come, come, follow me.

987
00:53:58,870 --> 00:54:00,740
You wanted to be alone, didn't you?

988
00:54:01,120 --> 00:54:02,320
But you can't escape from us.

989
00:54:02,320 --> 00:54:04,850
We sit even though we're not invited.

990
00:54:04,850 --> 00:54:05,970
Waiter, another table.

991
00:54:05,970 --> 00:54:07,260
May I? How are you, Marisa?

992
00:54:07,270 --> 00:54:08,460
-Fine, thanks.
-Twentytwo!

993
00:54:08,460 --> 00:54:10,470
They are 22 like the other years,
aren't they?

994
00:54:10,470 --> 00:54:13,180
-One single cake wouldn't be
enough for yours.   -Evil you are.

995
00:54:13,180 --> 00:54:15,050
I have a present for you, too.

996
00:54:15,050 --> 00:54:17,050
A proposal for South America.

997
00:54:17,610 --> 00:54:20,200
Don't spoil my birthday
with the same proposals of yours.

998
00:54:20,880 --> 00:54:22,250
We only miss South America, now.

999
00:54:22,260 --> 00:54:25,290
And we only miss that she puts
a spoke in our wheel.

1000
00:54:25,300 --> 00:54:28,650
I come to America with you
only if he makes me get angry.

1001
00:54:28,650 --> 00:54:29,860
So, let's hope for the best.

1002
00:54:30,250 --> 00:54:32,180
Doctor, are you singing for us tonight?

1003
00:54:32,190 --> 00:54:33,410
Why not? Give me the guitar.

1004
00:54:33,410 --> 00:54:35,990
There is one that really suits
with what is happening now.

1005
00:54:41,580 --> 00:54:44,290
Love was keeping me in chains,

1006
00:54:45,360 --> 00:54:47,930
but I said it was enough
and I got free.

1007
00:54:49,140 --> 00:54:50,650
The sky looks blue anymore.

1008
00:54:51,070 --> 00:54:52,340
The sun looks bright anymore.

1009
00:54:52,780 --> 00:54:55,740
And my heart is singing from happiness.

1010
00:54:56,290 --> 00:54:57,860
That girl, that girl,

1011
00:54:58,540 --> 00:55:00,980
She is telling me she wants to leave me.

1012
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:04,700
She thinks I'm swallowing a bitter pill.

1013
00:55:05,820 --> 00:55:08,400
She thinks I'll go crazy
and shoot myself.

1014
00:55:09,410 --> 00:55:10,780
That girl, that girl,

1015
00:55:11,630 --> 00:55:13,970
She doesn't know the favour
she makes me.

1016
00:55:14,850 --> 00:55:16,700
I'll find a prettier one

1017
00:55:16,700 --> 00:55:18,360
and alone she will be.

1018
00:55:18,420 --> 00:55:21,460
That girl, that girl, that girl!

1019
00:55:26,360 --> 00:55:28,890
Yesterday I got a letter

1020
00:55:29,820 --> 00:55:32,800
from the usher's daughter.

1021
00:55:33,460 --> 00:55:34,930
She writes she's not happy.

1022
00:55:35,440 --> 00:55:36,980
She'd like to make peace with me.

1023
00:55:37,320 --> 00:55:39,930
But I am enjoying my freedom.

1024
00:55:40,730 --> 00:55:42,340
That girl, that girl,

1025
00:55:42,780 --> 00:55:45,480
She is telling me she wants to leave me.

1026
00:55:46,580 --> 00:55:49,280
She thinks I'm swallowing a bitter pill.

1027
00:55:50,330 --> 00:55:53,280
She thinks I'll go crazy
and shoot myself.

1028
00:55:53,780 --> 00:55:55,400
That girl, that girl,

1029
00:55:55,900 --> 00:55:58,500
She doesn't know the favour
she makes me.

1030
00:55:59,620 --> 00:56:01,120
I'll find a prettier one

1031
00:56:01,120 --> 00:56:02,840
and alone she will be.

