01:09:34,120 --> 01:09:36,680
If you want to go the sanitarium,

1295
01:09:37,670 --> 01:09:39,980
-I will lead you.
-Yes, sir.

1296
01:09:41,990 --> 01:09:43,560
I can't believe.

1297
01:09:44,480 --> 01:09:46,850
Where are you from? Bergamo?

1298
01:09:49,380 --> 01:09:50,920
He didn't understand a word.

1299
01:09:52,090 --> 01:09:53,000
Do you know what we do?

1300
01:09:53,410 --> 01:09:54,530
This is the main square.

1301
01:09:55,310 --> 01:09:56,770
Let's sit here and she will pass by.

1302
01:09:56,770 --> 01:09:58,610
Are you crazy? This isn't a village.

1303
01:09:58,620 --> 01:09:59,560
This is a big city.

1304
01:09:59,560 --> 01:10:02,310
-What do we do then?
-Come with me, trust me, come with me.

1305
01:10:02,940 --> 01:10:03,910
What is that?

1306
01:10:04,290 --> 01:10:05,760
That may be the Titus' arc.

1307
01:10:05,980 --> 01:10:07,720
-Isn't it dangerous?
-No, it isn't.

1308
01:10:07,730 --> 01:10:09,630
It is so tall.

1309
01:10:33,350 --> 01:10:34,660
Excuse me, who are you looking for?

1310
01:10:34,660 --> 01:10:36,070
Miss Florian.

1311
01:10:36,070 --> 01:10:37,050
You're here, at last!

1312
01:10:37,050 --> 01:10:39,690
Listen you got to iron this,
Last changing room, n.10.

1313
01:10:39,930 --> 01:10:41,340
Quick, girls, it's late!

1314
01:10:41,340 --> 01:10:42,970
This time we'll be fined.

1315
01:10:42,970 --> 01:10:45,410
I'll make him a smile
and he won't fine us.

1316
01:10:46,910 --> 01:10:49,170
-All because of you.
-Easy, easy, let's go.

1317
01:10:49,170 --> 01:10:51,010
At last you came, what happened?

1318
01:10:59,660 --> 01:11:00,600
Come in.

1319
01:11:01,910 --> 01:11:02,580
May I?

1320
01:11:03,140 --> 01:11:05,240
The ironer. Come in, come in.

1321
01:11:05,240 --> 01:11:06,100
Come inside.

1322
01:11:07,060 --> 01:11:08,710
You'll find everything over there.

1323
01:11:10,310 --> 01:11:11,630
D'you know what I'm telling you?

1324
01:11:11,630 --> 01:11:13,020
Everyone has his own ideas.

1325
01:11:13,790 --> 01:11:16,140
Yes, but in the end there's
only one thing that matters.

1326
01:11:16,140 --> 01:11:17,150
Money!

1327
01:11:17,600 --> 01:11:18,790
If you don't have anything better.

1328
01:11:19,840 --> 01:11:22,850
Falling deeply in love must be
a real disgrace for you.

1329
01:11:23,640 --> 01:11:24,790
I think it's a fortune.

1330
01:11:26,640 --> 01:11:28,630
Excuse me, who is Miss Florian?

1331
01:11:29,210 --> 01:11:29,730
It's me.

1332
01:11:31,440 --> 01:11:32,070
Why?

1333
01:11:32,070 --> 01:11:33,610
No, nothing.

1334
01:11:34,020 --> 01:11:35,520
I think the iron is hot now.

1335
01:11:35,520 --> 01:11:36,920
Yes, yes, it is.

1336
01:11:38,750 --> 01:11:39,530
Hi Marisa.

1337
01:11:39,870 --> 01:11:40,820
A telegram from New York.

1338
01:11:41,020 --> 01:11:42,970
The producers will probably come tonight.

1339
01:11:43,440 --> 01:11:44,520
I appeal to you.

1340
01:11:44,970 --> 01:11:47,350
I've already told you
that I won't come to South America.

1341
01:11:47,350 --> 01:11:48,560
Ok, ok, we will see.

1342
01:11:48,560 --> 01:11:50,720
Marisa, would you ruin our careers, too?

1343
01:11:50,720 --> 01:11:52,790
Anyway, do me a favour,
be kind to them.

1344
01:11:52,790 --> 01:11:54,180
Induce them to sign.

1345
01:11:54,450 --> 01:11:55,310
I will finish them after.

1346
01:11:55,310 --> 01:11:57,540
Marisa, please, we depend on you.

1347
01:11:58,100 --> 01:11:59,510
Alright, what a drag!

1348
01:12:08,760 --> 01:12:11,240
Please, the tulle petticoats must be very stiff.

1349
01:12:11,250 --> 01:12:12,890
Alright, you'll be attended, Miss.

1350
01:12:13,220 --> 01:12:14,740
What a nice Milanese accent!

1351
01:12:15,210 --> 01:12:17,150
We, people from Napoli have a good ear.

1352
01:12:18,200 --> 01:12:20,470
We need just a few hours
and we learn.

1353
01:12:20,470 --> 01:12:22,190
Anyway, I adore the people from Napoli.

1354
01:12:22,190 --> 01:12:23,500
But I'm from the countryside.

1355
01:12:23,510 --> 01:12:24,620
Them expecially.

1356
01:12:25,410 --> 01:12:26,960
Maybe it's because I've a special reason.

1357
01:12:28,480 --> 01:12:30,370
Are you engaged to
some young man from there?

1358
01:12:31,200 --> 01:12:32,070
Did I guess?

1359
01:12:32,570 --> 01:12:36,180
Some nice, very rich, generous young man.

1360
01:12:36,950 --> 01:12:37,540
All true.

1361
01:12:37,540 --> 01:12:39,020
He's the best man in the world,

1362
01:12:39,020 --> 01:12:40,300
Only he is not rich, he's a student.

1363
01:12:40,300 --> 01:12:42,630
A student, o Lord,
what are you saying?

1364
01:12:43,230 --> 01:12:45,360
Sorry, but I am an old woman,

1365
01:12:45,900 --> 01:12:47,270
I could be your mother,

1366
01:12:47,660 --> 01:12:50,150
why do you want a moneyless
student to marry?

1367
01:12:50,930 --> 01:12:52,280
But I earn enough for two

1368
01:12:53,130 --> 01:12:55,050
Now you wanna offend that poor young man.

1369
01:12:55,050 --> 01:12:57,290
Do you think he'll accept to live with your money?

1370
01:12:58,030 --> 01:12:59,660
Then we will live with his few.

1371
01:13:00,720 --> 01:13:02,280
It's so easy to say...

1372
01:13:02,660 --> 01:13:04,710
Marisa, would you lend me your greasepaint?

1373
01:13:05,430 --> 01:13:07,530
-You always need something.
-That's it...

1374
01:13:13,770 --> 01:13:16,650
So, you could leave everything for him.

1375
01:13:17,540 --> 01:13:19,740
The theatre, the luxury.

1376
01:13:20,010 --> 01:13:21,780
When you fall in love, madam...

1377
01:13:22,660 --> 01:13:24,870
You're in deep trouble, my dear.

1378
01:13:26,020 --> 01:13:29,080
Either you ruin him,
or you ruin yourself.

1379
01:13:29,870 --> 01:13:31,990
Sorry, but I'm speaking from the heart.

1380
01:13:33,650 --> 01:13:36,010
I'd like to know why people thinks we are special.

1381
01:13:36,550 --> 01:13:39,870
Why? Can't I fall in love and marry me
like all the other girls?

1382
01:13:40,470 --> 01:13:42,080
Miss, you're really nice,

1383
01:13:42,080 --> 01:13:44,000
but, see, there is a reason.

1384
01:13:44,470 --> 01:13:47,420
For example, can you roll out the dough?

1385
01:13:47,820 --> 01:13:48,340
No.

1386
01:13:49,320 --> 01:13:51,830
If your husbands gets
an ink stain on his jacket,

1387
01:13:52,290 --> 01:13:53,290
do you know how to wash it?

1388
01:13:53,990 --> 01:13:54,470
No.

1389
01:13:54,950 --> 01:13:56,750
Have you ever made a washing?

1390
01:13:56,750 --> 01:13:58,130
No, I've never made it.

1391
01:13:58,430 --> 01:14:00,570
But I'll learn, and a lot of other things.

1392
01:14:01,510 --> 01:14:04,470
And there's one thing you reasonable
people will never learn.

1393
01:14:04,470 --> 01:14:06,170
What really loving each other is.

1394
01:14:06,510 --> 01:14:08,030
You can't even imagine it.

1395
01:14:08,490 --> 01:14:10,650
I love my boyfriend more than my life.

1396
01:14:11,140 --> 01:14:13,380
I could even be a maid,
for his love.

1397
01:14:13,380 --> 01:14:14,650
Ok, don't get angry.

1398
01:14:14,650 --> 01:14:17,150
I've spoken this way cause I'm a mother.

1399
01:14:20,090 --> 01:14:22,010
Miss, there's this gentleman,
do I let him in?

1400
01:14:22,450 --> 01:14:25,050
Ambrogio, I've told you not to let in anybody.

1401
01:14:25,610 --> 01:14:26,540
But this is an Earl.

1402
01:14:26,540 --> 01:14:30,350
I told you no one, except Mr. Gianni,
but he isn't coming tonight.

1403
01:14:35,020 --> 01:14:36,320
Are you married, aren't you?

1404
01:14:36,820 --> 01:14:37,640
I'm widow.

1405
01:14:38,710 --> 01:14:40,860
Did you know how to make everything
when you got married?

1406
01:14:41,330 --> 01:14:43,590
But we were of the same condition.

1407
01:14:44,290 --> 01:14:45,460
Who do you think I am?

1408
01:14:46,070 --> 01:14:49,480
Ny father was a village vet,
and he will be doctor, soon.

1409
01:14:49,500 --> 01:14:50,890
He will be it if he studies.

1410
01:14:51,610 --> 01:14:53,470
What do you think he's doing now?
Studying.

1411
01:14:54,180 --> 01:14:56,160
I he doesn't study, I don't wanna see him.

1412
01:15:01,020 --> 01:15:02,100
Do you need it now?

1413
01:15:02,910 --> 01:15:03,680
My dress! Yes.

1414
01:15:04,600 --> 01:15:05,430
Is it okay like this?

1415
01:15:06,010 --> 01:15:07,470
Yes, good!

1416
01:15:13,280 --> 01:15:14,520
How beautiful you are!

1417
01:15:15,030 --> 01:15:18,350
Now I understand why that student
lost his mind for you.

1418
01:15:19,190 --> 01:15:20,430
I lost it, too.

1419
01:15:21,410 --> 01:15:23,940
I'd make any sacrifice for Gianni's happiness.

1420
01:15:25,340 --> 01:15:26,090
His name is Gianni.

1421
01:15:33,140 --> 01:15:34,090
Good evening, miss.

1422
01:15:34,790 --> 01:15:35,520
How much I owe you?

1423
01:15:35,520 --> 01:15:36,240
Nothing.

1424
01:15:58,030 --> 01:15:58,850
Come, it's here.

1425
01:15:58,850 --> 01:16:00,170
I think it's here.

1426
01:16:00,660 --> 01:16:02,530
-At last!
-I can't walk anymore.

1427
01:16:03,430 --> 01:16:04,710
Yes, this is the stage.

1428
01:16:06,870 --> 01:16:08,240
Let's hope to find her.

1429
01:16:09,190 --> 01:16:10,450
Gentlemen, you can't stay here.

1430
01:16:10,910 --> 01:16:11,830
So sorry.

1431
01:16:14,230 --> 01:16:15,400
You can't stay there, too.

1432
01:16:16,550 --> 01:16:17,760
And you can't smoke.

1433
01:16:20,510 --> 01:16:21,900
And you can't go in.

1434
01:16:23,540 --> 01:16:24,660
And you can't speak.

1435
01:16:24,660 --> 01:16:27,120
Dear man, you are exaggerating, aren't you?

1436
01:16:27,120 --> 01:16:28,710
Don't go in, don't smoke,

1437
01:16:29,060 --> 01:16:29,880
don't speak,

1438
01:16:29,880 --> 01:16:32,210
I think this is too much.

1439
01:16:32,220 --> 01:16:33,560
Tell us what we can do.

1440
01:16:34,150 --> 01:16:37,710
First you have to tell me who you are,
what you want and what you look for.

1441
01:16:37,710 --> 01:16:39,540
What is this? A road block,
a frontier, a border?

1442
01:16:40,360 --> 01:16:42,270
Sorry, sorry, you're always behind...

1443
01:16:42,850 --> 01:16:44,910
There's more freedom in our country!

1444
01:16:44,910 --> 01:16:45,760
Unconditional.

1445
01:16:46,200 --> 01:16:48,020
But maybe you are the people from...

1446
01:16:48,020 --> 01:16:49,220
-Abroad!
-From the South.

1447
01:16:49,650 --> 01:16:50,840
I'm so sorry.

1448
01:16:51,790 --> 01:16:53,940
Miss Florian is waiting for you.

1449
01:16:55,460 --> 01:16:56,800
I hadn't realized.

1450
01:16:56,800 --> 01:16:58,480
Where is Miss Florian?

1451
01:16:59,060 --> 01:17:01,120
At the end of the corridor, on the right.

1452
01:17:01,120 --> 01:17:02,480
Changing room n.10.

1453
01:17:03,430 --> 01:17:08,600
-Next time we will see in our country...
-Let it go!

1454
01:17:08,630 --> 01:17:10,350
Who are they? The producers
from South America?

1455
01:17:10,700 --> 01:17:11,370
Yes, it's them.

1456
01:17:12,690 --> 01:17:14,590
Don't be a troublemaker.

1457
01:17:19,590 --> 01:17:20,440
Good evening gentlemen.

1458
01:17:21,230 --> 01:17:23,200
Remember me,
I'm the one who dances on tiptoe.

1459
01:17:23,200 --> 01:17:24,900
-Where do you dance?
-On tiptoe.

1460
01:17:25,280 --> 01:17:27,500
She says she dances on tiptoe...
Lucky her!

1461
01:17:27,980 --> 01:17:30,860
And I'm the one that does
the splits in the 2nd act.

1462
01:17:30,860 --> 01:17:32,210
That does the splits in the 2nd act.

1463
01:17:32,820 --> 01:17:34,280
-What does it mean?
-Are you asking to me?

1464
01:17:39,190 --> 01:17:41,650
-Two plus two is... is?
-Four!  -Four!

1465
01:17:50,450 --> 01:17:51,870
She says if you are thirsty
and want an olive.

1466
01:17:52,120 --> 01:17:53,490
-No, thanks.  -No, thanks.

1467
01:17:53,490 --> 01:17:54,500
Enjoy your meal.

1468
01:17:55,160 --> 01:17:56,040
Buenasera senor.

1469
01:17:56,830 --> 01:17:58,180
Would you give me a cigarette?

1470
01:17:59,440 --> 01:18:00,390
I don't smoke.

1471
01:18:00,390 --> 01:18:01,800
If you want to take a puff...

1472
01:18:04,440 --> 01:18:05,910
Another laugh near the pipe.

1473
01:18:07,410 --> 01:18:09,290
Unfortunately,
you won't see much of me tonight.

1474
01:18:09,820 --> 01:18:10,870
They cut my part.

1475
01:18:11,500 --> 01:18:12,260
What did they cut?

1476
01:18:12,260 --> 01:18:13,710
The part, the part.

1477
01:18:13,710 --> 01:18:14,720
Which one?

1478
01:18:14,720 --> 01:18:15,850
The best one.

1479
01:18:15,850 --> 01:18:19,500
-It's a pity so young...
-I'm so sorry for you.

1480
01:18:21,100 --> 01:18:22,400
-Marisa, they are here.
-Who?

1481
01:18:22,400 --> 01:18:25,550
The producers, the SouthAmericans,
they are so boorish!

1482
01:18:25,550 --> 01:18:26,560
Ok, let them in.

1483
01:18:26,940 --> 01:18:28,180
Please, come in.

1484
01:18:29,470 --> 01:18:31,600
-Here we are.
-Please, adelante, adelante.

1485
01:18:32,260 --> 01:18:34,000
Adelaide! Adelaide!

1486
01:18:35,600 --> 01:18:39,330
No, please, do come in,
please, please, come in.

1487
01:18:41,070 --> 01:18:43,400
Muy encantada, please,
take a seat,

1488
01:18:43,400 --> 01:18:46,800
forgive the mess of my room,
but it's work, you know.

1489
01:18:48,320 --> 01:18:52,980
You must forgive my Spanish but
I was in Barcelona a short 'tiempo'.

1490
01:18:54,070 --> 01:18:55,930
But you speak a little Italian, don't you?

1491
01:18:57,300 --> 01:18:58,890
Sometimes yes, sometimes not.

1492
01:18:58,890 --> 01:19:00,420
Not the Latin, not the Latin.

1493
01:19:00,760 --> 01:19:01,970
-Well, miss...
-Well

1494
01:19:02,400 --> 01:19:05,510
A moment, I'll speak
because I'm the elder.

1495
01:19:06,180 --> 01:19:10,820
Miss, with no offense,
we are serious persons.

1496
01:19:10,820 --> 01:19:13,150
persons that...
here we are.

1497
01:19:13,500 --> 01:19:17,230
I know, the vice-consul of Paraguay
told me a lot about you.

1498
01:19:17,540 --> 01:19:18,580
-Who's him?
-Paraguay?

1499
01:19:18,580 --> 01:19:20,120
Do you know this guy?

1500
01:19:20,550 --> 01:19:22,680
He must be someone we met by chance.

1501
01:19:23,180 --> 01:19:26,800
Indeed, nobody says bad things about us.

1502
01:19:26,800 --> 01:19:29,100
We were waiting for you,
we got your telegram.

1503
01:19:30,080 --> 01:19:33,810
Did you send a telegram?

1504
01:19:33,810 --> 01:19:35,680
-Who sent this telegram?
-I didn't!  -Neither did I!

1505
01:19:36,020 --> 01:19:37,830
-Who sent it?
-It must have been someone for you.

1506
01:19:38,200 --> 01:19:39,850
-Who can he be?
-Mezzacapa!

1507
01:19:40,240 --> 01:19:41,330
He never minds his own business.

1508
01:19:41,620 --> 01:19:44,670
That one! You don't know Mezzacapa!

1509
01:19:44,670 --> 01:19:46,920
By the way, we want to deal with
the conditions, don't we?

1510
01:19:46,920 --> 01:19:47,990
Which conditions?

1511
01:19:48,710 --> 01:19:50,200
The financial conditions.

1512
01:19:51,940 --> 01:19:53,000
Here we have som...

1513
01:19:53,000 --> 01:19:55,200
It's not the right time,
not the right time.

1514
01:19:55,860 --> 01:19:56,480
Let's hear.

1515
01:19:56,730 --> 01:20:00,650
I have many expenses, the dresses,
the costumes, my life tenor...

1516
01:20:00,720 --> 01:20:01,560
Also the tenor?

1517
01:20:01,820 --> 01:20:02,560
Is there a tenor, too?

1518
01:20:02,950 --> 01:20:05,050
Ok, it means that we'll provide
for the tenor as well.

1519
01:20:05,390 --> 01:20:06,310
Did you bring some small change?

1520
01:20:06,310 --> 01:20:07,860
I will speak with the tenor, ok?

1521
01:20:08,990 --> 01:20:10,230
I wanted to ask you:

1522
01:20:10,240 --> 01:20:14,110
Are things quiet in the South?
No revolutions a-coming?

1523
01:20:15,010 --> 01:20:18,040
Are we joking?
Revolutions in the South?

1524
01:20:18,540 --> 01:20:21,610
Because I read in the newspapers
about some movement...

1525
01:20:22,240 --> 01:20:23,750
Even this they put in the newspapers!

1526
01:20:23,750 --> 01:20:26,890
-The journalists...  -That is nonsense,
nothing to be worried about.

1527
01:20:27,640 --> 01:20:31,220
That has to do with our enemy,
Mezzacapa.

1528
01:20:32,600 --> 01:20:35,250
So, you are interested in politics.

1529
01:20:35,530 --> 01:20:37,680
Sometimes, we break his windows.

1530
01:20:37,690 --> 01:20:40,020
Break his windows, but we're joking.

1531
01:20:40,020 --> 01:20:43,770
-And he shoots us.  -He's a hunter,
so he shoots us.

1532
01:20:44,130 --> 01:20:45,900
And Gianni... you know.

1533
01:20:46,960 --> 01:20:47,560
Gianni?

1534
01:20:48,640 --> 01:20:49,800
What does Gianni have to do with this?

1535
01:20:50,010 --> 01:20:51,810
He does. Gianni is our nephew.

1536
01:20:53,690 --> 01:20:55,410
How? So you are...

1537
01:20:55,980 --> 01:20:57,270
Gianni's nephews.

1538
01:20:57,750 --> 01:20:58,920
Nephews' Giannis.

1539
01:20:59,200 --> 01:21:01,650
The nephew... We are the neph...
the nephew...

1540
01:21:02,080 --> 01:21:03,510
Gianni has a nephew...

1541
01:21:03,820 --> 01:21:04,830
And who is this nephew?

1542
01:21:05,220 --> 01:21:06,020
-Speak!  -Speak!

1543
01:21:06,650 --> 01:21:07,380
Excuse him.

1544
01:21:07,820 --> 01:21:08,720
He makes me confuse.

1545
01:21:09,360 --> 01:21:11,090
We are Gianni's uncles.

1546
01:21:11,470 --> 01:21:12,540
Gianni is nephew to us.

